Higginbotham was sent off as early as the 10th minute for a shoulder barge into the neck and head area of Rebels lock Matt Phillip. JOHANNESBURG- The Queensland Reds and captain Scott Higginbotham were dealt a blow, after the player was banned for three weeks for a dangerous tackle during their 45-19 loss to the Melbourne Rebels in their season opener. Higginbotham was sent off as early as the 10th minute for a shoulder barge into the neck and head area of Rebels lock Matt Phillip, forcing the Reds to play the rest of the game with 14 men on the park. Higginbotham pleaded guilty to the dangerous tackle charge by SANZAAR and will now miss the next three weeks of action. WATCH: Higginbotham sent off against Rebels 